Romantic city of Mostar but often underestimated! Tell me what you think about it ? A destination on your travel list..? 

Mostar, Bosnia & Herzegovina 🇧🇦

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Senna Relax on August 17, 2021. May be an image of nature and tree.

node.text:
Una National Park is all about water with a network of river streams, pools, white water rapids, canyons and waterfalls that are surrounded by lush forests with dense vegetation and limestone cliffs. The rich flora and fauna include rare medicinal plants as well as endangered animals such as lynx, bears and wolves. 

The story goes that the Una river got its name from a Roman warrior that thought the river was so beautiful that it was the one and only (Una). (I agree that is really one of most beautiful rivers I’ve seen)

Una National Park is the perfect place for outdoor activities like rafting, kayaking, swimming, mountain biking and hiking. In addition, the park also has some cultural and historical heritage with ancient citadels, monasteries and mosques.

Despite it’s natural beauty, Una National Park still receives a small number of visitors. Especially compared to nearby Plitvice National Park in Croatia that lies only 35 kilometers away. Part of the reason is that in Bosnia, Una National Park is a bit remote and difficult to get to but if you follow road which get you all along the river, you’d  stop at each corner you’ll find!

However, those who make the effort, will be rewarded with one of the most beautiful areas in Bosnia. If you are looking for a peaceful and quiet spot full of nature that is off the beaten path, Una National Park is the place to go and it is a worthwhile addition to any Bosnia itinerary. 

#HelloFrom #BosniaAndHerzegovina #Bosnia #UnaNationalPark
